Title.String: CBS News/New York Times Monthly Poll #1, September 1995

Label.Content: NO DEALINGS WITH CRIMINAL JUSTICE SYSTEM
VOTED, WON'T SAY FOR WHOM OR OTHER
IN AN smash CONSISTING OF JUST ONE COUNTY

LiteralText.Text: 1. DO YOU APPROVE OR DISAPPROVE OF THE WAY BILL CLINTON IS HANDLING HIS JOB AS PRESIDENT?
2. DO YOU APPROVE OR DISAPPROVE OF THE WAY BILL CLINTON IS HANDLING THE SITUATION IN BOSNIA?
3. DO YOU APPROVE OR DISAPPROVE OF THE UNITED STATES AND NATO CONDUCTING AIR STRIKES ON BOSNIAN SERB POSITIONS IN RESPONSE TO SERB SHELLING OF THE MARKET PLACE IN SARAJEVO (sara-YEA-vo) LAST WEEK?

5. HOW MUCH CONFIDENCE DO YOU HAVE THAT THE AMERICAN CRIMINAL JUSTICE SYSTEM GENERALLY MAKES THE RIGHT DECISIONS ABOUT WHO'S GUILTY AND WHO'S INNOCENT -- A GREAT DEAL OF CONFIDENCE, SOME CONFIDENCE, NOT MUCH CONFIDENCE, OR NO CONFIDENCE?

6. IN GENERAL, DO YOU THINK THE AMERICAN CRIMINAL JUSTICE SYSTEM IS BIASED IN FAVOR OF THE PERSON ACCUSED OF A CRIME, IS BIASED AGAINST THE PERSON ACCUSED OF A CRIME, OR DOES THE CRIMINAL JUSTICE SYSTEM GENERALLY TREAT THE ACCUSED PERSON FAIRLY?
7. HOW MUCH CONFIDENCE DO YOU, YOURSELF, HAVE IN THE POLICE IN YOUR COMMUNITY -- A GREAT DEAL, QUITE A LOT, SOME, OR VERY LITTLE?

8. IF YOU HAD SOME TROUBLE WITH THE POLICE -- A TRAFFIC VIOLATION MAYBE, OR BEING ACCUSED OF A MINOR OFFENSE -- DO YOU THINK THAT MOST LIKELY YOU WOULD BE GIVEN A HARDER TIME THAN OTHER PEOPLE, WOULD BE TREATED ABOUT THE SAME AS ANYONE ELSE, OR WOULD BE TREATED A LITTLE BETTER THAN MOST PEOPLE?
9. SOME PEOPLE SAY THE POLICE DON'T SHOW RESPECT FOR PEOPLE, OR THEY USE INSULTING LANGUAGE. HAS THIS EVER HAPPENED TO YOU?
10. DO YOU GENERALLY THINK OF THE POLICE MORE AS FRIENDS, MORE AS ENEMIES, OR DON'T YOU THINK OF THEM IN EITHER OF THESE WAYS?
11. IN GENERAL, DO YOU THINK THE CRIMINAL JUSTICE SYSTEM IN THE UNITED STATES IS BIASED IN FAVOR OF BLACKS, OR IS IT BIASED AGAINST BLACKS, OR DOES IT GENERALLY GIVE BLACKS FAIR TREATMENT?
12. DO YOU THINK THE POLICE IN MOST BIG CITIES ARE GENERALLY TOUGHER ON WHITES THAN ON BLACKS, OR TOUGHER ON BLACKS THAN ON WHITES, OR DO THE POLICE TREAT THEM BOTH THE SAME?
15. IN GENERAL, DO YOU THINK THE NEWS MEDIA IN THE UNITED STATES IS BIASED IN FAVOR OF BLACKS, OR IS IT BIASED AGAINST BLACKS, OR DOES IT GENERALLY GIVE BLACKS FAIR TREATMENT?
16. HOW CLOSELY HAVE YOU FOLLOWED RECENT NEWS ABOUT O.J. SIMPSON AND THE MURDERS HE IS CHARGED WITH? WOULD YOU SAY YOU HAVE FOLLOWED IT VERY CLOSELY, SOMEWHAT CLOSELY, NOT TOO CLOSELY, OR NOT AT ALL?
17. DO YOU THINK IT IS POSSIBLE FOR O.J. SIMPSON TO GET A FAIR TRIAL ON THOSE CHARGES IN LOS ANGELES, OR DON'T YOU THINK A FAIR TRIAL IS POSSIBLE?
18. FROM WHAT YOU'VE HEARD OR READ SO FAR, DO YOU THINK O.J. SIMPSON IS PROBABLY GUILTY OF THE CRIMES HE HAS BEEN CHARGED WITH, IS PROBABLY NOT GUILTY, OR DON'T YOU KNOW ENOUGH ABOUT IT YET TO SAY?
18A. IF YOU HAD TO SAY, DO YOU THINK O.J. SIMPSON IS PROBABLY GUILTY OR PROBABLY NOT GUILTY?
19. IN THIS CASE SO FAR, DO YOU THINK THE CRIMINAL JUSTICE SYSTEM HAS BEEN BIASED IN FAVOR OF O.J. SIMPSON, OR HAS IT BEEN BIASED AGAINST O.J. SIMPSON, OR HAS IT BEEN TREATING O.J. SIMPSON FAIRLY?
20. IN GENERAL, DO YOU THINK THE NEWS MEDIA HAVE BEEN TOO HARSH IN THEIR COVERAGE OF O.J. SIMPSON, TOO EASY IN THEIR COVERAGE OF O.J. SIMPSON, OR HAVE THE NEWS MEDIA TREATED O.J. SIMPSON FAIRLY?
21. IN THE O.J. SIMPSON CASE, DO YOU THINK JUDGE LANCE ITO IS GENERALLY BEHAVING FAIRLY AND PROPERLY, OR NOT?
21A. DO YOU THINK JUDGE ITO IS FAVORING THE DEFENSE, IS FAVORING THE PROSECUTION, OR DON'T YOU THINK JUDGE ITO IS FAVORING ONE SIDE OR THE OTHER?

Q22. THE DEFENSE LAWYERS IN THIS CASE HAVE SAID THAT THERE WAS A CONSPIRACY BY MEMBERS OF THE LOS ANGELES POLICE DEPARTMENT TO PLANT BLOOD AND OTHER EVIDENCE TO MAKE O.J. SIMPSON LOOK GUILTY OF THESE TWO MURDERS. HOW LIKELY DO YOU THINK IT IS THAT THERE WAS A CONSPIRACY BY MEMBERS OF THE LOS ANGELES POLICE DEPARTMENT IN THIS CASE -- VERY LIKELY, SOMEWHAT LIKELY, NOT VERY LIKELY, OR NOT AT ALL LIKELY?

23. WHAT ABOUT MARK FURHMAN ACTING ALONE? HOW LIKELY DO YOU THINK IT IS THAT MARK FURHMAN PLANTED THE BLOODY GLOVE OR OTHER EVIDENCE TO MAKE O.J. SIMPSON LOOK GUILTY? DO YOU THINK THAT IS VERY LIKELY, SOMEWHAT LIKELY, NOT VERY LIKELY, OR NOT AT ALL LIKELY?
25. MY LAST FEW QUESTIONS ARE FOR BACKGROUND ONLY. IN THE LAST YEAR, HAVE YOU OR ANY MEMBER OF YOUR IMMEDIATE FAMILY BEEN THE VICTIM OF A CRIME?
26. DO YOU PERSONALLY KNOW ANY POLICE MAN OR POLICE WOMAN IN YOUR AREA?

27. HAVE YOU, YOURSELF EVER HAD ANY DEALINGS WITH THE CRIMINAL JUSTICE SYSTEM, AND BY THAT I MEAN POLICE, OTHER LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICIALS, JUDGES, PROSECUTORS OR COURT OFFICERS? (IF YES) AT ANY TIME DURING THOSE DEALINGS, DID YOU FEEL YOUR CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS WERE VIOLATED IN ANY WAY, OR WERE YOUR CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS ALWAYS RESPECTED?
28. DO YOU FREQUENTLY LISTEN TO POLITICAL CALL-IN SHOWS ON RADIO, OR DON'T YOU?
41. CBS NEWS [FILL PAPR] MAY WANT TO CALL YOU BACK SOMETIME TO ASK MORE OF YOUR OPINIONS. IN ORDER TO MAKE SURE WE REACH YOU AGAIN, MAY I HAVE YOUR FIRST NAME ONLY. (MAXIMUM 8 CHARACTERS)
31. GENERALLY SPEAKING, DO YOU USUALLY CONSIDER YOURSELF A REPUBLICAN, A DEMOCRAT, AN INDEPENDENT, OR WHAT?
32. DO YOU THINK OF YOURSELF AS CLOSER TO THE REPUBLICAN PARTY OR TO THE DEMOCRATIC PARTY?
33. HOW WOULD YOU DESCRIBE YOUR VIEWS ON MOST POLITICAL MATTERS? GENERALLY DO YOU THINK OF YOURSELF AS LIBERAL, MODERATE, OR CONSERVATIVE?
29. SOME PEOPLE ARE REGISTERED TO VOTE AND OTHERS ARE NOT. ARE YOU REGISTERED TO VOTE IN THE PRECINCT OR ELECTION DISTRICT WHERE YOU NOW LIVE, OR AREN'T YOU?

30. DID YOU VOTE FOR PRESIDENT IN 1992, DID SOMETHING PREVENT YOU FROM VOTING, OR DID YOU CHOOSE NOT TO VOTE FOR PRESIDENT IN 1992? IF VOTED, ASK: DID YOU VOTE FOR GEORGE BUSH, BILL CLINTON, OR ROSS PEROT?
35. WHAT WAS THE LAST GRADE IN SCHOOL YOU COMPLETED?
36. HOW OLD ARE YOU?
36A. ARE YOU BETWEEN 18 AND 29, 30 AND 44, 45 AND 64, OR ARE YOU OVER 64?
37. ARE YOU WHITE, BLACK, OR SOME OTHER RACE?
37A. ARE YOU OF HISPANIC ORIGIN OR DESCENT, OR NOT?
38. WAS YOUR TOTAL FAMILY INCOME IN 1994 UNDER OR OVER $30,000? 38A. WAS IT UNDER OR OVER $15,000? 38B. WAS IT BETWEEN $30,000 AND $50,000, OR BETWEEN $50,000 AND $75,000 OR WAS IT OVER $75,000?

39. ARE THERE ANY OTHER TELEPHONE NUMBERS IN YOUR HOME THAT I COULD HAVE DIALED AND REACHED YOU ON -- I DON'T MEAN EXTENSIONS, BUT DIFFERENT TELEPHONE NUMBERS? IF NECESSARY SAY: WE NEED TO KNOW HOW HARD OR EASY IT IS TO REACH PEOPLE.
40. NOW I DIALED YOU AT [FILL AREA]-[FILL PRFX:0]-[FILL SUFX:0], HOW MANY OTHER NUMBERS ARE THERE IN YOUR HOME?
34. WHAT IS YOUR RELIGIOUS PREFERENCE [UNDERLINE] TODAY [NORMAL]?
